T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(10. Collection and Scraping Method) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Preferred workflow:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Manually collect official source URLs.) Tj
T*
(2. Record every reviewed URL in `source_inventory.csv`.) Tj
T*
(3. Use simple scraping only for public pages.) Tj
T*
(4. Save raw extracted text in `raw_pages/` when possible.) Tj
T*
(5. Manually clean and chunk the useful text.) Tj
T*
(6. Annotate every chunk with topic, audience, risk level, and usage mode.) Tj
T*
(7. Validate JSONL before handoff.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Recommended Python tools:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    requests) Tj
T*
(    beautifulsoup4) Tj
T*
(    trafilatura) Tj
T*
(    pandas) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Basic scraping example:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    import requests) Tj
T*
(    from bs4 import BeautifulSoup) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    url = "https://example.edu/page") Tj
T*
(    html = requests.get\(url, timeout=20\).text) Tj
T*
(    soup = BeautifulSoup\(html, "html.parser"\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    for tag in soup\(["script", "style", "nav", "footer", "header"]\):) Tj
T*
(        tag.decompose\(\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    text = soup.get_text\("\\n"\)) Tj
T*
(    lines = [line.strip\(\) for line in text.splitlines\(\) if line.strip\(\)]) Tj
T*
(    clean_text = "\\n".join\(lines\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Do not trust scraper output directly. Every final chunk should be manually) Tj
ET
